      intentionally submitted to the Licensor for inclusion in the Work.

   f) “Source Code” means the preferred form of the Work for making
      modifications, including all modules, scripts, configuration files,
      and interface definitions.

   g) “Object Code” means any compiled, assembled, or otherwise mechanically
      transformed form of the Source Code that is executable on a computer.

   h) “Derivative Work” means any work, whether in Source Code or Object
